The financial institutions under Finance and Insurance sector contracted by -2.48 per cent in the fourth quarter 2020 from 6.80 per cent in third quarter 2020 and 22.33 per cent in fourth quarter 2019, an analysis of the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) has shown. According to NBS, the Gross Domestic Product (GDP) report Q4 2020, the financial institutions in Q4 2019 to Q4 2020, financial institutions under Financial and Insurance sector grew by 13.34 per cent in full year 2020 from 2.4 per cent in 2019 and 1.41 per cent in 2018. A breakdown of the report, however, showed that the insurance sector in one year between Q4 2019 to Q4 2020 contracted by -14.3 per cent in Q4 2020 from -18.67 per cent in Q3 2020 and 3.21 in Q4 2019. The analysis further showed that insurance between 2017 and 2020 contracted by -15.3 per cent in full year 2020 from 3.59 per cent in 2019 and 6.12 per cent in 2018. Meanwhile, the Financial and Insurance sector contracted by -3.63 per cent in Q4 2020 from 3.21 per cent in Q3 2020 and 20.18 per cent in Q4 2019. Overall, the Financial and Insurance sector grew by 9.37 per cent in full year 2020 from 2.56 per cent in 2019 and 2.03 per cent in 2018. The report further read: “The Finance and Insurance sector consists of the two subsectors, Financial Institutions and Insurance, which accounted for 91.40 per cent and 8.60 per cent of the sector respectively in real terms in Q4 2020. Growth in this sector, in real terms, totaled –3.63 per cent, lower than the rate recorded in Q4 2019, and the rate recorded in the preceding quarter. Quarter on quarter, real growth stood at 26.07 per cent. “Annual growth of 9.37 per cent was recorded in 2020, compared to 2.57 per cent in 2019. The contribution of Finance and Insurance to real GDP stood at 3.07 per cent, lower than the contribution of 3.19 per cent recorded in the fourth quarter of 2019 by –0.12 per cent points, but higher than 2.67 per cent recorded in Q3 2020 by 0.40 per cent points. The annual sectoral contribution recorded in 2020 was 3.36 per cent. As a whole, the sector grew at –1.10 per cent in nominal terms (year on year), with the growth rate of Financial Institutions as 0.07 per cent while –12.05 per cent was recorded for insurance. “The overall rate was lower than in Q4 2019 by –24.43 per cent points, and –7.01 per cent points than the preceding quarter. Quarter on quarter growth was 26.88 per cent while annual growth of this sector was 11.98 per cent in 2020. The sector’s contribution to the overall nominal GDP was 2.80 per cent in Q4 2020, lower than the 3.12 per cent it represented a year earlier, but higher than the contribution of 2.46 per cent it made in the preceding quarter. For 2020, the sector contributed 3.11 per cent of aggregate nominal GDP”, the NBS said.